hpnicfEvb.name: hpnicfEvb
hpnicfEvb.description: EVB management information base for managing devices that support Ethernet Virtual Bridging. This MIB is an extension of IEEE8021-EVB-MIB.

hpnicfEvbSetResult.name: hpnicfEvbSetResult
hpnicfEvbSetResult.description: If a set operation on EVB-MIB-tables returns success, this object indicates the actual result of this operation. Otherwise, it is meaningless. unknown: The set operation on the node has been completed, but the result could only be got from the table which the set operation happended. processing: The set operation is in process. Another set operation cannot be performed at this time. success: The set operation has succeeded. failed: The set operation has failed.

hpnicfEvbDefaultManagerTable.name: hpnicfEvbDefaultManagerTable
hpnicfEvbDefaultManagerTable.description: A table that contains configuration information for the default Virtual Station Interface (VSI) manager.

hpnicfEvbDefaultManagerEntry.name: hpnicfEvbDefaultManagerEntry
hpnicfEvbDefaultManagerEntry.description: A list of objects containing information for the default VSI manager.

hpnicfEvbManagerIndex.name: hpnicfEvbManagerIndex
hpnicfEvbManagerIndex.description: Index of the default manager table.

hpnicfEvbManagerType.name: hpnicfEvbManagerType
hpnicfEvbManagerType.description: Type of the default VSI manager. ipv4: Specifies the IPv4 address of the default VSI manager. ipv6: Specifies the IPv6 address of the default VSI manager. name: Specifies the name of the default VSI manager, a case-insensitive string of 1 to 127 characters. local: Specifies the device as the default VSI manager.

hpnicfEvbManagerID.name: hpnicfEvbManagerID
hpnicfEvbManagerID.description: Default VSI manager. The value is zero-length string when the VSI manager type is 'local'.

hpnicfEvbManagerPort.name: hpnicfEvbManagerPort
hpnicfEvbManagerPort.description: Port number of the default VSI manager. Optional when the VSI manager type is not 'local'. If the VSI manager type is 'local', it returns zero.

hpnicfEvbManagerRowStatus.name: hpnicfEvbManagerRowStatus
hpnicfEvbManagerRowStatus.description: Row status: CreateAndGo, Active, or Destroy.

hpnicfEvbPortConfigTable.name: hpnicfEvbPortConfigTable
hpnicfEvbPortConfigTable.description: A table that contains configuration information for the EVB bridge port.

hpnicfEvbPortConfigEntry.name: hpnicfEvbPortConfigEntry
hpnicfEvbPortConfigEntry.description: A list of objects containing information for the EVB bridge port.

hpnicfEvbSchannelConfigTable.name: hpnicfEvbSchannelConfigTable
hpnicfEvbSchannelConfigTable.description: A table that contains configuration information for the S-channel.

hpnicfEvbSchannelConfigEntry.name: hpnicfEvbSchannelConfigEntry
hpnicfEvbSchannelConfigEntry.description: A list of objects containing information for the S-channel.

hpnicfEvbSchannelSVLAN.name: hpnicfEvbSchannelSVLAN
hpnicfEvbSchannelSVLAN.description: S-VLAN ID. 0 means that the S-channel is not bound to any S-VLAN. 1 represents the SVID for the default S-channel S-channel 1.

hpnicfEvbMacLearningStatus.name: hpnicfEvbMacLearningStatus
hpnicfEvbMacLearningStatus.description: The MAC address learning function is enabled or not.

hpnicfEvbRRStatus.name: hpnicfEvbRRStatus
hpnicfEvbRRStatus.description: The RR mode for the S-channel is enabled or not.

hpnicfEvbSchannelRowStatus.name: hpnicfEvbSchannelRowStatus
hpnicfEvbSchannelRowStatus.description: Row status: CreateAndGo, Active, or Destroy.

hpnicfEvbVSIConfigTable.name: hpnicfEvbVSIConfigTable
hpnicfEvbVSIConfigTable.description: A table that contains configuration information for the VSI.

hpnicfEvbVSIConfigEntry.name: hpnicfEvbVSIConfigEntry
hpnicfEvbVSIConfigEntry.description: A list of objects containing information for the VSI.

hpnicfEvbSBPPortNumber.name: hpnicfEvbSBPPortNumber
hpnicfEvbSBPPortNumber.description: The Station-facing Bridge Port (SBP) port number.

hpnicfEvbVSICommand.name: hpnicfEvbVSICommand
hpnicfEvbVSICommand.description: This object indicates the association or pre-associate property of the VSI.

hpnicfEvbVSIIsActive.name: hpnicfEvbVSIIsActive
hpnicfEvbVSIIsActive.description: The VSI is activated or not. Activate a VSI after configuring a VSI filter, and deactivate a VSI before removing a VSI filter.

hpnicfEvbVSIRowStatus.name: hpnicfEvbVSIRowStatus
hpnicfEvbVSIRowStatus.description: Row status: CreateAndGo, Active, or Destroy.

hpnicfEvbVSIFilterConfigTable.name: hpnicfEvbVSIFilterConfigTable
hpnicfEvbVSIFilterConfigTable.description: A table that contains configuration information for filters of the VSI.

hpnicfEvbVSIFilterConfigEntry.name: hpnicfEvbVSIFilterConfigEntry
hpnicfEvbVSIFilterConfigEntry.description: A list of objects containing information for filters of the VSI.

hpnicfEvbVSIMac.name: hpnicfEvbVSIMac
hpnicfEvbVSIMac.description: The MAC address part of the MAC/VLANs for a VSI.

hpnicfEvbVSIVlanId.name: hpnicfEvbVSIVlanId
hpnicfEvbVSIVlanId.description: The VLAN ID part of the MAC/VLANs for a VSI.

hpnicfEvbVSIFilterRowStatus.name: hpnicfEvbVSIFilterRowStatus
hpnicfEvbVSIFilterRowStatus.description: Row status: CreateAndGo, Active, or Destroy.

hpnicfFlex10PortConfigTable.name: hpnicfFlex10PortConfigTable
hpnicfFlex10PortConfigTable.description: A table that contains configuration information for the flex10 bridge port.

hpnicfFlex10PortConfigEntry.name: hpnicfFlex10PortConfigEntry
hpnicfFlex10PortConfigEntry.description: A list of objects containing information for the flex10 bridge port.

hpnicfFlex10PortEnableStatus.name: hpnicfFlex10PortEnableStatus
hpnicfFlex10PortEnableStatus.description: The flex10 function is enabled or not.

hpnicfFlex10RemoteSchannelTable.name: hpnicfFlex10RemoteSchannelTable
hpnicfFlex10RemoteSchannelTable.description: A table that contains remote S-channel details.

hpnicfFlex10RemoteSchannelEntry.name: hpnicfFlex10RemoteSchannelEntry
hpnicfFlex10RemoteSchannelEntry.description: A list of objects describing remote S-channels.

hpnicfFlex10RemSchDesFormat.name: hpnicfFlex10RemSchDesFormat
hpnicfFlex10RemSchDesFormat.description: Description format of the remote S-channel.

hpnicfFlex10RemSchTerminationType.name: hpnicfFlex10RemSchTerminationType
hpnicfFlex10RemSchTerminationType.description: Termination type of the remote S-channel. 0: PCI Physical Function (Primary). 1: SRIOV Virtual Function. 2: PCI Physical Function (Secondary). 3: Virtual Switch Port. 4: NCSI Port. 2147483647: This value means a Description TLV with format 0 has not been received. other: Unknown termination type.

hpnicfFlex10RemSchTerminationCap.name: hpnicfFlex10RemSchTerminationCap
hpnicfFlex10RemSchTerminationCap.description: Termination capabilities of the remote S-channel. If a Description TLV with format 0 has not been received, it returns all zeros.

hpnicfFlex10RemSchTrafficClass.name: hpnicfFlex10RemSchTrafficClass
hpnicfFlex10RemSchTrafficClass.description: Traffic classes of the remote S-channel. If a Description TLV with format 0 has not been received, it returns all zeros.

hpnicfFlex10RemSchCir.name: hpnicfFlex10RemSchCir
hpnicfFlex10RemSchCir.description: Committed Information Rate (CIR) of the remote S-channel. If a Description TLV with format 0 has not been received, it returns 0.

hpnicfFlex10RemSchPir.name: hpnicfFlex10RemSchPir
hpnicfFlex10RemSchPir.description: Peak Information Rate (PIR) of the remote S-channel. If a Description TLV with format 0 has not been received, it returns 0.

hpnicfFlex10RemSchConnectionID.name: hpnicfFlex10RemSchConnectionID
hpnicfFlex10RemSchConnectionID.description: Connection instance ID of the remote S-channel. The value is a zero-length string if a Description TLV with format 1 has not been received. Otherwise it returns a string with length 16.

hpnicfFlex10SchannelLinkCtlTable.name: hpnicfFlex10SchannelLinkCtlTable
hpnicfFlex10SchannelLinkCtlTable.description: A table that contains link status information for the S-channel.

hpnicfFlex10SchannelLinkCtlEntry.name: hpnicfFlex10SchannelLinkCtlEntry
hpnicfFlex10SchannelLinkCtlEntry.description: A list of objects containing information for the S-channel.

hpnicfFlex10SchannelLocalStatus.name: hpnicfFlex10SchannelLocalStatus
hpnicfFlex10SchannelLocalStatus.description: Link status of the local S-channel.

hpnicfFlex10SchannelRemoteStatus.name: hpnicfFlex10SchannelRemoteStatus
hpnicfFlex10SchannelRemoteStatus.description: Link status of the remote S-channel.
